ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.FormAndInfoAndMaterialsTxt: MOST OF THE FOUNDATION'S GRANTS ARE THROUGH INDIVIDUAL AWARDS OR AWARDS UNDER AUTHORIZATION THAT INVOLVE PROGRAM CENTERS, COORDINATING CENTERS OR HUBS. THESE ISSUES AND TOPICS OF INTEREST ARE DESCRIBED ON THE FOUNDATION'S INTERNET SITE (WWW.RWJF.ORG). THE COMPETITIVE GRANT APPLICATION PROCESS BEGINS WITH A CALL FOR PROPOSAL OR A REQUEST FOR PROPOSAL, WHICH CAN BE FOUND ON THE FOUNDATION'S INTERNET SITE. MOST OF THE FOUNDATIONS GRANTS ARE SOLICITED BY THE FOUNDATION, AND GENERALLY EITHER FIT THE FOUNDATION'S EXPLICIT FIELDS OF INTEREST WITHIN HEALTH AND HEALTH CARE, OR ADVANCE THE FOUNDATIONS OVERARCHING GOAL OF BUILDING A CULTURE OF HEALTH IN AMERICA. APPLICANTS MAY INITIATE THE GRANT PROCESS BY SUBMITTING A THREE-PAGE, ELECTRONIC BRIEF PROPOSAL USING THE APPLICATION FORM PROVIDED ON-LINE.
ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.SubmissionDeadlinesTxt: NO DEADLINES, EXCEPT WHEN FOUNDATION ISSUES A CALL FOR PROPOSAL (CFP) OR REQUEST FOR PROPOSAL (RFP).
ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.RestrictionsOnAwardsTxt: THE ROBERT WOOD JOHNSON FOUNDATION'S MISSION IS TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH AND HEALTH CARE OF ALL AMERICANS AND TO BUILD A CULTURE OF HEALTH THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY - ENABLING ALL IN OUR DIVERSE SOCIETY TO LEAD HEALTHY LIVES, NOW AND FOR GENERATIONS TO COME.
